40|$|The current article {{presents}} the first data on physical-chemical parameters of wet precipitation collected at single collection {{point in the}} city of Rio Grande, during the period of 12 months in 1997 - 1998. The employed technique of <b>rainwater</b> <b>separation</b> into several portions made clear the process of the atmosphere self-purification during a precipitation event. The pH of rainwater depends on the extent of industrial emissions and increases during a precipitation event. The first portion of rainwater shows an obvious neutralizing effect of soil and ocean-derived components, whose intensity depends on the duration of the preceding dry period...|$|E

